    <div class="section">
        <h2>Symptoms</h2>
        <p>
            Symptoms of celiac disease vary widely among people, which can make it hard to recognize. Some people
            don’t notice any symptoms at all. They also may be different in children and adults. The most common
            symptoms include:
        </p>
        <div class="section flex-section" style="justify-content: space-between;">
            <ol>
                <li>Pain and bloated stomach.</li>
                <li>Gas.</li>
                <li>Constipation.</li>
                <li>Diarrhea.</li>
                <li>Nausea and vomiting.</li>
                <li>Weight loss.</li>
                <li>Mouth ulcers.</li>
                <li>Damage to tooth enamel.</li>
                <li>Anemia, usually from iron deficiency due to decreased iron absorption.</li>
            </ol>
            <div class="image">
                <img src="/img/info/Screenshot 2025-03-11 152057.png" alt="Celiac Disease Illustration">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


